    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Awesome! Do you feel like writing a tutorial that we would publish on our [blog](https://blog.algolia.com/)? This seems to be like one of the most advanced usages of instantsearch.js that we did. Contact me at vincent@algolia.com if interested.\n\n> Obviously it triggers a lot of queries/renders though so not sure how performant it will be.\n\nYes indeed that's why I proposed a solution where only the count is updated, not all the widgets. And then only update the whole interface when switching tabs. That's still feasible.\n\nWe might have to re-think about this usecase once we have more feedback from you to see what could be done.\n\n> The only outstanding issue is that the searchbox is not updating when the query changes. Is there a way to trigger a re-render or manually set it?\n\nYes this is a known issue that I fixed yesterday, should be released soon (see #886)\n\nIn the meantime you can update the value of the input manually with DOM:\n\n``` js\ndocument.querySelector('#search-box input').value = ..;\nhelper.setQuery(..).search();\n```\n\nDoes that makes sense?\n",
